Dear SUM,

I don't think that we are right for each other. I need someone who doesn't think that Picasso is a brand of pasta, SUM. You are so mind-numbingly boring that even your dog falls asleep when you come home. Maybe you'd be less boring once I got to know you more, but I don't want to take that chance. You're about as much fun as watching a troupe of chimpanzees vomiting over each other. The best thing I can say about sex with you is that it was mercifully brief. Your mind is like concrete; thoroughly mixed up and permanently set. You're a person of few words: "Myself, Me and I." There's nothing wrong with you that couldn't be cured with a little Prozac and a polo mallet. Nevertheless, you continue to show a great deal of promise, and maintain an unbroken record of broken promises. You always wanted to be somebody, but you should have been more specific. No offence, but you dressed like a clown at an out-of-season funfair. SUM, if you are thinking of replying to this letter, save your breath - you'll need it to inflate your next date. But you could try calling call me some day, so I can have the pleasure of hanging up on you. I'd like to say it's been fun knowing you, but neither of us believe that. 

Adios Asshole,
